          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the due date for filing Softex?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "SOFTEX forms are filed monthly, within 30 days of the last invoice raised in that month, rather than separately for each invoice. Once STPI certifies the form it goes to the authorised dealer bank so the inward remittance can be matched. Delayed filing leaves the export outstanding in the bank EDPMS records, which blocks closure of the entry."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between a SOFTEX form and a shipping bill?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A shipping bill is filed with Customs for goods that physically cross the border, while a SOFTEX form covers software and IT enabled services transmitted electronically, where no physical consignment exists for Customs to assess. Both serve the same purpose under FEMA, which is to create an official record of the export against which the foreign remittance is reconciled."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is Softex filing mandatory?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes, filing is mandatory for software and IT enabled service exports transmitted through data links, under the Foreign Exchange Management Act 1999 and the RBI Master Direction on export of goods and services. The requirement applies to STPI units, SEZ units and units outside those schemes alike, and certification is done by STPI or by the SEZ authority for SEZ exporters."
          }
        }
